com.karusmc.xmc.commands

Class DispatchCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bukkit.command.Command
      • com.karusmc.xmc.core.XMCommand
        • com.karusmc.xmc.commands.DispatchCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Dispatcher, org.bukkit.command.PluginIdentifiableCommand

    public class DispatchCommand
extends XMCommand
implements Dispatcher
    Default implementation of a Dispatcher/Command delegation command. This class determines and delegates execution to a command instance stored internally through a chain of responsibility when called.
    Author:
    PanteLegacy @ karusmc.com

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public void execute(org.bukkit.command.CommandSender sender,
                    String[] args)
        Checks if the number of arguments is greater than or equal to 1 and there is a command instance registered with the name specified by the first argument, before trimming the arguments and delegating command execution to the command instance. Note that this method does not check if the player has the appropriate permissions needed and instead delegates it along with execution to the command instance. Abstract method that implementations should override
        Specified by:
        execute in class XMCommand
        Parameters:
        sender - the CommandSender instance
        args - the command argument
